# CODEOWNERS — FirneyGroup/mcp-broker
#
# Code owners review the listed paths before merge. Combined with branch
# protection (Settings → Branches → main → "Require review from Code Owners"),
# this gates changes that could otherwise widen the secret-exposure surface.
#
# Last entry per path wins. Use directory-globs (trailing slash) to scope to
# the dir, file-globs (no slash) to scope to that specific file.

# Workflow files determine what runs in CI and what secrets are injected. A
# malicious edit here can exfiltrate CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN or any other
# repo/org secret. Gate every change.
/.github/workflows/   @AshleyMaloney

# CODEOWNERS itself — prevent silent removal of the gate.
/.github/CODEOWNERS   @AshleyMaloney

# Dependency manifests — supply-chain risk. A malicious package addition or
# version bump can introduce a backdoor that runs in CI with secret access.
/pyproject.toml       @AshleyMaloney
/uv.lock              @AshleyMaloney

# Security policy + project invariants — operator-visible documents that
# downstream users rely on.
/SECURITY.md          @AshleyMaloney
/AGENTS.md            @AshleyMaloney
